explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the relationship between banking market structure and funding liquidity risk, using empirical methods such as the system generalized method of moments (GMM) estimator, random-effect model, and corrected least square dummy variable (LSDVC) technique. There is no mention of any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models in the title or abstract. The study is grounded in econometrics and financial analysis rather than machine learning or artificial intelligence.
